From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000005 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thingino Project
Date: Thu, 17 Jul 2025 21:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] motor: remove kfree(mdev) to fix double-free

motor_probe() allocates mdev with devm_kzalloc(), which is
automatically freed by the kernel devres framework on device unbind.
The original motor_remove() also calls kfree(mdev), causing a
double-free that corrupts the kernel heap.

This bug was latent because motor_probe() was never called until
of_match_table was added. Now that the driver actually probes,
the double-free triggers on module unload/reboot.

Remove the manual kfree and let devm handle it.

Signed-off-by: Thingino Project
---
--- a/4.4.94/misc/motor/motor.c
+++ b/4.4.94/misc/motor/motor.c
@@ -933,7 +933,6 @@ static int motor_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	misc_deregister(&mdev->misc_dev);
 
-	kfree(mdev);
 	return 0;
 }
 
